# Live Log Updates

The project has a local live log at `upcoming-notes.md` (root). Update it when:

- The user says "add to the log", "log this", "add to upcoming notes", or similar
- We fix a bug — add a Changelog entry and mark the bug as `[FIXED]` under Bugs
- We complete a planned change — add a Changelog entry
- The user reports a new bug — add under Bugs with `[OPEN]` and a brief plan
- The user shares a plan or idea — add under Upcoming plans or Backlog / ideas

**Format conventions:**
- **Changelog:** `YYYY-MM-DD — One-line summary.` (newest first)
- **Bugs:** `[OPEN]` or `[FIXED]` — short title. Optional next line: plan or "Fixed by: …"
- **Plans:** Short title, optional `→ .cursor/plans/….plan.md`
- **Backlog:** One line per idea
- Use `YYYY-MM-DD` for dates. Keep entries one line when possible.
